text: Well, <@U02USELSBRT> I respect your thoughts, but here's my take.  Marketing does not equal promotion. I Understand when you say Product > Marketing cause product is before marketing and not above in priority.                                                                               And the Same goes with sales, there are Sales and Marketing departments in businesses for a reason, if they were not needed there wouldn't be one.                       Again a great product is a must but that doesn't mean it is enough.                               Also when you talk about PLG, most PLG strategies involve the same research marketing does for your Org and the same tactics that Marketers do.    Marketing and Sales in 2022 are not like the Era of Yellow Pages when you would gather a bunch of leads and shoot them up. It's about building an audience, educating the customers, positioning above competitors, resolving customer objections and Sales is about building relationships with Buyer Centric Conversations.
